{"source_key":"sha256-1d9c4047d1264fa94471600951d6dcb4","record_index":43,"record_hash":"sha256:9a849bc67cb46418ccb218e97118429c497a16f15c2b3514639a6f57897e29b4","timestamp":"2026-05-29T18:04:06.585Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: fbd51a\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2894\nOutput:\n# Findings: PR 13996 erroneously picks up PR 13995's agent session\n\n## Summary\n\nPR [#13995](https://trail.but.dev/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/13995) and PR\n[#13996](https://trail.but.dev/gitbutlerapp/gitbutler/pull/13996) were\nimplemented at the same time in one shared GitButler workspace (two applied\nstacks), with no overlapping code. Each PR should surface only its own agent\nsession. PR 13995 does. PR 13996 surfaces **both** sessions, and the wrong one\n(13995's) even matches at the stronger *review* evidence tier, so it sorts\nfirst.\n\n**The defect is in `but-agentlog`'s read/matching logic, not in capture and not\nin agent-trail.** Specifically, the \"strong association\" heuristic\n`environment_promotes_worktree_to_target` in\n`crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs` is fooled because GitButler's worktree\nsnapshot is **workspace-global and not attributed to a stack/session**. When two\nsessions work concurrently in one shared worktree, one session's dirty files\nappear in the other session's snapshots; when the first session commits them to\nits branch, the second session is falsely credited with \"activity\" on that\nbranch and its review.\n\n- **Capture (`but-agentlog` write side): correct.** It faithfully recorded that\n  the workspace ambiently had both stacks applied and that the shared worktree\n  held those dirty files.\n- **agent-trail: not the cause.** `project_pr` just calls\n  `find_related_sessions_limited` for the review and branch targets and renders\n  the result; it adds no relatedness logic of its own.\n- **`but-agentlog` read/projection matching: the bug.**\n  `environment_promotes_worktree_to_target` in\n  `crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs`.\n\n---\n\n## The two real sessions\n\nIn `gitbutler/.git/git-meta.sqlite` there are two sessions relevant here:\n\n| Session | Work | Turns |\n|---|---|---|\n| `[REDACTED:entropy]` | PR **13995** (`agent-status-after-default`) | 31 |\n| `sha256-2aa\n[TRUNCATED]\nhere the fix belongs (not implemented)\n\nThe disambiguating data exists but is discarded before the matcher sees it:\nGitButler knows hunk → stack assignment (`hunk_assignments` table in\n`gitbutler/.git/gitbutler/but.sqlite`), but the environment snapshot flattens all\ndirty files into one global `worktree.files` list with no stack attribution.\n\nThe fix belongs in `but-agentlog`'s read/capture-interpretation layer, not in\nagent-trail. Options, in rough order of robustness:\n\n1. Attribute worktree files to the stack they are assigned to before the promote\n   check, so another stack's dirty files in the shared worktree cannot satisfy\n   \"this session promoted them to target X.\"\n2. Require the promotion to involve a stack this session actually edited (e.g.\n   correlate with the session's own tool edits / file writes for that turn),\n   rather than any-file-anywhere in the global worktree.\n3. Address the commit-then-open-PR fragility in the same pass: the legitimate\n   owner currently only reaches branch-tier evidence for its own PR because the PR\n   is attached to the branch after the commit lands and the worktree is clean by\n   then. Consider letting a strong branch-level promotion carry to the review\n   target once that branch's review becomes known, so the real owner is not\n   demoted below an ambient match.\n\n## Evidence handles (internal)\n\n- 13995 session: `[REDACTED:entropy]` (31 turns)\n- 13996 session: `sha256-2aa7526ee83b80afcc1a21d18443cec0` (8 turns)\n- Triggering transition: `c13f` t28 (2026-05-29T16:28:09) → t29 (16:35:30)\n- Triggering commit: `3e25ea72c1` on `unapply-v3-settings-toggle`\n- Key code:\n  - `crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs` — `session_has_target_activity`,\n    `environment_promotes_worktree_to_target`, `commit_contains_worktree_file`,\n    `target_appearance_is_specific`\n  - `crates/but-agentlog/src/environment.rs:568` — `path_fingerprint`\n  - `crates/but-agentlog/src/projection.rs` — `project_pr` (review + branch\n    target construction, evidence tiers)\n","tool_name":"exec_command","tool_kind":"exec","tool_input":null,"exit_code":0,"outcome":"succeeded","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T18:04:06.585Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}